Package com.jenmann.entity

Class Characters

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jenmann.entity.Characters
  • @Entity(name="Characters")
public class Characters
extends java.lang.Object
    The Characters class is really supposed to be the Character class, but Character is also a significant type in Java, so I made this classname plural. Each instance represents an individual Dungeons and Dragons character. One user can have many characters.
    Author:
    jcmann
